elements.name: As a user, I should be able to delete a planet I added without an associated moon using a valid id, so that my planetarium is up to date
elements.description: System should check that the given planet id is the primary key for an existing planet created by the user with no associated moons, and remove that planet from the planetarium if so.

steps.name: The user is logged in
The user sets the dropdown to display the planet creation menu
The user enters "3" as the celestial body to be deleted
The user presses the delete button
The planet with the id "3" should be deleted from the Planetarium

elements.name: As a user, I want to be able to remove planets from the planetarium by their name so that we can stop tracking them
elements.description:
This is to verify that we can remove planets if we pass in their name, spelled correctly and with the correct case. And that the user will see that the planet and it's orbiting moon is no longer within the planetarium
